---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ImageLightbox from '../components/ImageLightbox.astro';
import createUserSwagger from '../screenshots/Create_User_Swagger.PNG';
import loginUserSwagger from '../screenshots/Login_User_Swagger.PNG';
import githubWebhook from '../screenshots/Github_Webhook.PNG';
import updatedRepoWebhook from '../screenshots/Updated_Repo&Webhook.PNG';
---

<Layout title="Abaki - AI-Powered GitHub Repository Monitor">
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-12 md:py-20">
        <a href="/" class="mb-8 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-medium text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300">
            <span class="mr-2">&larr;</span>
            Back to Portfolio
        </a>

        <article>
            <header class="mb-12">
                <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl text-white">
                    Abaki Project
                </h1>
                <p class="text-lg text-gray-400">
                    A comprehensive .NET 8 REST API for monitoring GitHub repositories with AI-powered code auto-fixing
                </p>
            </header>

            <section class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8">
                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Project Overview</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                        Abaki is a full-featured backend API built with .NET 8 that monitors GitHub repositories and 
                        automatically detects and fixes code quality issues using AI. The system integrates with the GitHub API, 
                        connects to an external Python AI service, manages encrypted API keys, and provides real-time updates 
                        via SignalR WebSockets.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mt-4">
                        I built this system from scratch as part of my diploma work, handling all core architecture decisions 
                        and implementation details. The codebase demonstrates enterprise-level patterns including secure authentication, 
                        external API integration, async streaming, database design, and real-time communication.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Core Technology Stack</h2>
                    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
                        {[
                            '.NET 8', 
                            'C#', 
                            'Entity Framework Core', 
                            'SQLite', 
                            'JWT Authentication', 
                            'SignalR',
                            'Serilog',
                            'Octokit',
                            'BCrypt',
                            'AES Encryption'
                        ].map((tech) => (
                            <span class="rounded-full border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-500/10 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-indigo-300">
                                {tech}
                            </span>
                        ))}
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Key Features</h2>
                    <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-300">
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3 font-bold">→</span>
                            <span><strong>User Authentication:</strong> Secure registration/login with JWT tokens and BCrypt password hashing</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3 font-bold">→</span>
                            <span><strong>GitHub Integration:</strong> Repository CRUD, webhook management, and real-time event handling</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3 font-bold">→</span>
                            <span><strong>AI Code Auto-Fix:</strong> Streaming communication with Python AI service for code repairs</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3 font-bold">→</span>
                            <span><strong>Database Architecture:</strong> Entity Framework Core with SQLite, migrations, and relationships</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3 font-bold">→</span>
                            <span><strong>Encrypted Key Management:</strong> AES encryption for GitHub and AI provider tokens</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3 font-bold">→</span>
                            <span><strong>Structured Logging:</strong> Serilog with file rotation and real-time updates via SignalR</span>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Project Screenshots</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                        These visuals capture the most relevant parts of the Abaki workflow, from user authentication to GitHub webhook setup and repository updates.
                    </p>
                    <ImageLightbox
                        images={[
                            {
                                src: createUserSwagger,
                                alt: 'Swagger UI for registering a new Abaki user',
                                caption: 'Registration endpoint in Swagger for creating a new user.'
                            },
                            {
                                src: loginUserSwagger,
                                alt: 'Swagger UI for logging in to Abaki',
                                caption: 'Login endpoint response for authenticating into Abaki.'
                            },
                            {
                                src: githubWebhook,
                                alt: 'Abaki GitHub webhook configuration view',
                                caption: 'GitHub webhook setup and repository integration overview.'
                            },
                            {
                                src: updatedRepoWebhook,
                                alt: 'Updated repository and webhook status in Abaki',
                                caption: 'Repository and webhook update state after configuration.'
                            }
                        ]}
                    />
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Featured Portfolio Pieces</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                        The Abaki project is broken down into 6 focused portfolio pieces, each highlighting a key architectural 
                        component and the learning journey behind it:
                    </p>
                    <div class="space-y-3">
                        <a href="/abaki-auth" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-500/5 hover:bg-indigo-500/10 transition">
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">1. User Authentication & JWT Security</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Secure registration, password hashing with BCrypt, JWT token generation, and claim-based authorization</p>
                        </a>

                        <a href="/abaki-github" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-500/5 hover:bg-indigo-500/10 transition">
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">2. GitHub Repository Integration</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Octokit integration, CRUD operations, webhook setup, and real-time GitHub event handling</p>
                        </a>

                        <a href="/abaki-autofix" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-500/5 hover:bg-indigo-500/10 transition">
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">3. AI-Powered Code Auto-Fix Engine</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Async streaming HTTP client, real-time token processing, error resilience, and AI service communication</p>
                        </a>

                        <a href="/abaki-database" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-500/5 hover:bg-indigo-500/10 transition">
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">4. Database & Entity Framework Architecture</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Entity relationships, migrations, model configuration, and query optimization patterns</p>
                        </a>

                        <a href="/abaki-encryption" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-500/5 hover:bg-indigo-500/10 transition">
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">5. API Key Management & Encryption</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">AES encryption implementation, deterministic encryption for queries, secure token storage, and key rotation</p>
                        </a>

                        <a href="/abaki-logging" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-500/5 hover:bg-indigo-500/10 transition">
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">6. Activity Logging & Real-time SignalR Hub</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Structured logging with Serilog, file rotation, WebSocket-based real-time log streaming to clients</p>
                        </a>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Learning Outcomes</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                        Building Abaki taught me valuable lessons about:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span>Enterprise-level API architecture and design patterns</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span>Secure credential management and encryption practices</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span>Async/await patterns and streaming HTTP communication</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span>Third-party API integration and error resilience</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span>Database modeling and Entity Framework optimization</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span>Real-time communication with WebSockets</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span>Structured logging and observability patterns</span>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Project Impact</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                        Abaki demonstrates my ability to design and implement a complete, production-ready backend system 
                        from the ground up. The project showcases full-stack API development with modern .NET practices, 
                        integration with external services, security best practices, and proper software architecture. 
                        This was a significant learning experience that prepared me for real-world backend development challenges.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>
        </article>
    </main>
</Layout>
